    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-19T18:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-19T18:32:00-05:00" n="317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/5–1754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d317fn1">Drafted by <persName>Jones</persName>, cleared with
                        the Bureau of European Affairs and the Bureau of Far Eastern Affairs,
                        approved for transmission by <persName corresp="#p_POPPERDH1"
                            >Popper</persName>, and signed by Assistant Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName>. <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>’s
                        clearance was indicated by <persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName>’s
                        handwritten notation: “Cleared with <persName corresp="#p_DRUMRIGHTEF1"
                            >Drumright</persName>”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-19T19:32:00-04:00"
                            >May 19, 1954—7:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>567. Re <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> elections (<gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss>s 678 and 732): Department recognizes desirability earliest
                    possible decision these elections and importance of timing and hopes formulate
                    position near future. However in view whole political situation particularly
                    Indochina and Geneva believe we should keep position flexible and make no
                    commitments for the moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
